-- Spain Negotiating EU Funds for Banks, Economista Says
-- B y   B e n   S i l l s
-- 2012-05-10T07:54:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-05-10/spain-negotiating-efsf-eib-funds-for-banks-el-economista-says.html
(Corrects name of EU facility in first paragraph.)  The Spanish government is negotiating
with European Union officials over funding from the European
Financial Stability Facility or the  European Investment Bank  to
bolster its lenders, El Economista reported.  Officials favor tapping the EIB for funding to dodge the
conditions that  Germany  may impose for access to the EFSF, the
newspaper said, citing unidentified people close to Prime
Minister  Mariano Rajoy .  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
